Facebook games marketing report.¬†Link
Norway's U4 anti-corruption centre did a study pointing¬†out that most statistics quoted about the scale of corruption are either very weakly-sourced or just made-up. Beware of 'decorative statistics'.¬†Link¬†(PDF)
Amazon ad-supported video has 120 million viewers a month.¬†Link
The BBC now publishes a register of all on-air talents' eternal gigs.¬†Link
Last and of course most important - preliminary data from Flurry on how many people opt-in to ATT data collection in iOS 14.5.¬†Link


























PREVIEW FROM THE PREMIUM EDITION


























Paid content
We started paying for content a decade or s ago, but pay walls only worked¬†for big sites and Apple's frictionless micropayments only worked for games (if that). Now there‚Äôs another payment moment. Lots of buzzy startups, from Substack (probably niche) to Clubhouse (unproven) to Onlyfans, Cameo, Scroll or indeed Twitter, explore ways to get people to pay. Meanwhile, these are all also a swing of the cycle from bundling to unbundling - just as blogs unbundled media and then (mostly) got aggregated back up, now these companies let individual creators go direct, but this time get paid.¬†

